IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: On Thursday, November 23, 2023, at approximately 1240 hours, I, Trooper C. Cooper #7501, responded to 5628 Cokesbury Road, Rhodesdale, Dorchester County, Maryland 21659, in reference to an assault. While en route to the above mentioned location, I was contacted by Sgt. B. Dadds #551, who advised me that the victim was sexually assaulted by her mothers boyfriend. Sgt. B. Dadds also advised that the alleged victim and mother were outside of the residence in the middle of the field waiting for our arrival. Along with this information, Sgt. B. Dadds advised that the victim was extremely intoxicated and autistic. Upon arrival I located the alleged victim, identified as Ashley Holston and her mother, identified as Julie Holston seated at the edge of a clearing to the right of the residence. As I approached both individuals, Ashley began to walk towards me. I advised Ashley that my body worn camera was activated, therefore the interaction was being recorded. I asked Ashley what had happened at which time she stated she was not comfortable telling me. I advised Ashley that I can understand that this is a difficult and awkward situation but I needed as many details as she could provide me. Ashley stated that she was asleep on the love seat within the living room of the residence when she awoke to her mothers boyfriend, identified as Dennis White standing over top of her. Ashley stated that she was wearing pink shorts and they had been pulled down by Dennis. Ashley stated that Dennis was performing oral sex to her and holding her down. Ashley stated shortly after she woke up to this her mom, identified as Julie Holston, entered the residence through the front door and witnessed Dennis standing over her. Ashley stated that she yelled for her mother and asked for help. Ashley stated that Julie exited the residence and began to scream. Ashley stated that Dennis created separation from her and began to follow Julie outside. Ashley stated she also ran outside through the front door in an attempt to get to Julie. Ashley stated during this time Dennis was also outside following them stating please dont call the cops. Ashley stated that Dennis went back inside the residence and she and Julie sat outside waiting for us to arrive. Note that while speaking with Ashley I detected the strong odor of an alcoholic beverage emanating from Ashleys breath and person. After speaking with Ashley I made contact with Julie who was seated in a small black kayak in the middle of a clearing to the right of the residence. Julie appeared to be upset and was holding back tears. While introducing myself to Julie I again detected the strong odor of an alcoholic beverage emanating from her breath and person. Julie stated that she made everyone breakfast on todays date (11/23/2023) and after doing so, Dennis and Ashley fell asleep in the living room. Julie stated that Ashley was asleep on the loveseat and Dennis was on the couch. Julie stated when she observed this she knew Ashley was putting herself in a vulnerable position because Dennis had attempted to sexually assault her a couple weeks prior. Julie stated that she exited the residence through the front door to smoke a cigarette and call a friend. Julie stated when she was done outside she reentered the residence through the front door and observed Dennis to be standing over Ashley with his penis out. Julie stated it appeared that Dennis was attempting to put his penis in Ashleys mouth while she was sleeping. Julie stated that Dennis saw her and stumbled away from where Ashley was sleeping and stated he was trying to get his lighter out of his pants. Julie stated that she told Ashley to get up and she responded Mommy, I cant! Julie stated she did not understand why she could not get up so she exited the residence screaming. Julie stated that both Ashley and Dennis followed her. Julie stated that Ashley was yelling Mommy while Dennis was telling her not to call the cops. Julie stated that is when she dialed 9-1-1. I then asked Julie where Dennis was located at which time she stated he was passed out on the couch drunk. Julie stated that Dennis consumes nearly a 30 pack of beer and two handles of liquor a day. Julie then requested to go inside the residence to retrieve a cigarette. I asked Julie where they were located and she stated in her bedroom. I requested to come in the residence in order to make contact with Dennis and ensure no further altercation occurred, Julie then denied me consent to come inside and asked where I would be located. I informed Julie I would stand in the living room between her and Dennis and she stated, that is okay, I will just run in and get my cigarette then come back out with the front door open. Julie then entered the residence and retrieved her cigarettes. After this initial conversation with Ashley and Julie I made contact with Cpl. Townsend of CED, who was en route to our location. I advised Cpl. Townsend of the information I had gathered, at which time he told me to hold what I had and he would be on scene in approximately 15 minutes. While waiting for Cpl. Townsend, both Ashley and Julie continued to get into arguments and yell at one another to the point they had to be separated. Ashley remained on the front step of the residence and Julie went back to the kayak she was originally seated in. I approached Julie once more in an attempt to gain knowledge of how autistic Ashley was. Julie stated that Ashleys autism is more exaggerated when she is intoxicated. Julie stated her current state was as severe as it would get. Julie stated that Ashley is able to maintain herself on her own accord but does ask that she be with her throughout the day. Julie stated that she believes it is more of a comfort and security than it is the need for her to be there and assist her. During this conversation with Julie, Ashley repeatedly stated that she hated the police and did not know why we were there. I then asked Julie if she knew of Ashley and Dennis having a consensual sexual relationship in the past, at which time she stated I do not think so but she did not know for sure. At this time Cpl. Townsend arrived on scene and took over the investigation. Myself, Cpl. Moore and Trp. Walker stood with Julie while Cpl. Townsend conducted an interview with Ashley. Once Ashley completed her interview Cpl. Townsend began one with Julie. I interrupted the interview to see if Cpl. Townsend wanted me to start the initial report for charges at which time he stated yes. I then sat in my patrol vehicle and began to type. While typing Cpl. Moore and Trp. Walker stood with Ashley who was seated on the front steps of the residence. After about five minutes of typing I heard Trp. Walker said something but did not hear it clearly. I exited my vehicle at the same time as TFC. Davis arrived on scene. I then asked what was going on at which time Cpl. Moore advised that someone was walking in the woods at the front of the residence. Note the woodline was a small hedgerow that had a cut corn field on the other side of it. I then walked into the cut corn field while Cpl. Moore and TFC. Davis walked along the other side. I was advised that the unknown subject was a white male, wearing a camouflage shirt and black pants. Shortly after this notification Ashley looked inside the residence and stated that Dennis was gone. I then notified the barrack and requested that they contact the Dorchester Sheriffs Office and request additional units to respond to our location in order to set up a perimeter. While walking the field attempting to see Dennis, Cpl. Townsend advised that contact was made with the Dorchester County States Attorney Office who stated that he had obtained enough evidence for an on-view arrest. During this time contact was made with the Caroline County Sheriffs Office who had a K-9 unit working that was capable of tracking. DFC. Wolf and his partner Ludi responded to the scene. While they were en route Trooper 6 also contacted the barrack and asked if we needed their assistance. Trooper 6 was eventually granted permission and came overhead to scan the area. DFC. Wolf and Ludi arrived on scene, made contact with Cpl. Townsend and began a track. During the initial track there was a miscommunication on possibly seeing Dennis in the woodline. After regathering, DFC. Wolf began the track again and was able to locate Dennis laying in the woods. DFC. Wolf and Trp. Walker gave Dennis commands at which time he complied and was placed under arrest by Trp. Walker. Dennis was then placed in the front seat of TFC. Davis patrol vehicle per department policy. Dennis was transported to the Maryland State Police - Easton I Barrack for booking and processing. Prior to leaving the scene I was advised by Cpl. Townsend to seize a crossbow and machete that belonged to Dennis for safekeeping. Cpl. Townsend advised that he did not trust Ashley and Julie with the crossbow and the machete was laying underneath Dennis on the couch, where he was allegedly sleeping. I then transported the crossbow, which can be identified as a Center Point 370 Sniper (S/N: 1116M00017) and the machete, a black Ka-Bar machete to the Maryland State Police - Easton I Barrack. Once at the barrack I processed both items for safekeeping and placed them within the temporary storage. Cpl. Townsend continued his investigation by interviewing Dennis at the barrack. See his supplement for further information in regards to the case. All above events occurred in Dorchester County, Maryland.
